result.text:
Would you pay nearly $3 million for a bottle of liquor?
A Scotch whisky nearly 100 years old sold at auction in London on Saturday for $2.7 million. That's a record for a bottle of wine or spirits and works out to about $170,000 per shot.
The whisky was distilled in 1926 by Macallan and aged 60 years in sherry casks. Only 40 bottles were produced in 1986, and only 12 of those (including the one sold Saturday) had labels designed by Italian painter Valerio Adami.
One of the 12 was drunk, and another was destroyed in an earthquake.
Will Saturday's anonymous buyer open the bottle? The tasting manager at a Soho whisky shop said, "We are not here too long. Enjoy your life. Please drink it. Tell us what it tastes like."
#Macallan #Scotchwhisky #WhiskyRecord #MacallanAdami1926

result.text:
Elon Musk on Saturday vowed a "thermonuclear lawsuit" as big-name advertisers fled X over antisemitic content on his social media platform.
IBM, Apple, Disney and others suspended advertising after a watchdog group, Media Matters, reported that X has positioned some ads next to pro-Nazi posts.
In addition, Musk drew widespread criticism, including from the White House, for endorsing a post that said Jews were pushing "hatred against whites." 
On Saturday, Musk urged his millions of followers to "Stand with X to protect free speech." He said the lawsuit would be against Media Matters and others involved in what he called "this fraudulent attack on our company."
Perhaps in an effort to calm things down, he also posted that "calls for extreme violence" on X will result in suspension. He cited the Palestinian rallying cry "from the river to the sea," saying it implies genocide.
X, formerly known as Twitter, has seen a steady loss of advertisers and users since Musk bought the platform a year ago. He also owns Tesla and SpaceX.
#X #ElonMusk #MediaMatters #Antisemitism
